[size=2][b][anchor=save]3.0 - PlayerSave.java[/b][/size]

To start off, look for:

[/center]
[code=java]
	} else if (token.equals("character-rights")) {
		   p.playerRights = Integer.parseInt(token2);
[/code]
[center]

Add below it:

[/center]
[code=java]
					} else if (token.equals("character-here")) {
						p.playerhere = Integer.parseInt(token2);
[/code]
[center]

What you did is add your quest to be operable in your characters file (So that the player only does it once). 

Now, search for:

[/center]
[code=java]
             characterfile.newLine();
             characterfile.write("character-rights = ", 0, 19);
             characterfile.write(Integer.toString(p.playerRights), 0, Integer.toString
[/code]
[center]
Add:
[/center]
[code=java]
			characterfile.write("character-here = ", 0, 19);
			characterfile.write(Integer.toString(p.playerhere), 0, Integer.toString(p.playerhere).length());
			characterfile.newLine();
[/code]
[center]
You now setup a basic int that checks the player file and see's were the player is up to in the quest.

